evidence: The gamma photon from Tc-99m has an energy of about 140 kilo-electronvolts.

concepts.term: after a half-life of about six hours, it transitions to the stable form Tc-99, releasing a gamma photon in the process

evidence: The radionuclide 99mTc, which is the most widely used radionuclide, used in over 90% of studies, exists in such a metastable state. It is formed from 99Mo according to the scheme shown below. Roughly 90% of the metastable 99mTc nuclei follow this decay path: 99Mo → β + 99mTc → 99gTc + γ
